Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: pybecker
Version: 0.0.2
Summary: pybecker is a library to control becker RF shutters.

pybecker enables you to open, close or stop your shutter.
Home-page: https://github.com/nicolasberthel/pybecker
Author: Nicolas Berthel
Author-email: contact@nicolasberthe.fr
License: GNU GPLv3
Download-URL: https://github.com/nicolasberthel/pybecker
Description: pybecker - controling Becker shutters with Python
        ============================================
        
        This library is based on the work of **ole1986** (https://github.com/ole1986/centronic-py)

        PyBecker requires a Becker Centronic USB Stick in order to communicate with the Shutters.
        The pairing need as well to be performed before and is not yet part of the library

        
